Kafka encourages us to think about EVENTS (i.e the things that happen at a specific point of time)
Events form the backbone of contemporary data systems and kafka is the infrastructure used to manage them.
-- kafka is focussed on processing events in realtime.  distributed event processing. 
Kafka track logs of events. These logs are called the topics. So, they just do not consist of present state, but includes the history of values over a period 
of time. 
The messages in topics are immutable

We can create database schemas that model this.
tables, relational databaases do not do this so well with log type use cases

So, kafka uses log files instead of tables. We call them messages. These logs are called topics in kafka.
Kafka is schemaless. Messages are just bytes of data.
With immutable topic, we can absolutely transform it.

Topic is not a queue. its a log.
Kafka is composed of network of machines, called BROKERS. 

We would need kafka brokers in conventional systems. 
If we are using kafka in confluent cloud , we do not need any kafka server.
Brokers are responsible to write incoming messages, 

